        <detaileddescription>
<para>save an object tree to a given file file format must be scene-capable Generated from function <computeroutput>MR::ObjectSave::toAnySupportedSceneFormat</computeroutput>. Parameter <computeroutput>object</computeroutput> can not be null. It is a single object. Parameter <computeroutput>file</computeroutput> is a UTF-8 encoded filesystem path. Parameter <computeroutput>settings</computeroutput> is a single object. Parameter <computeroutput>settings</computeroutput> has a default argument: <computeroutput>{}</computeroutput>, pass a null pointer to use it. Never returns null. Returns an instance allocated on the heap! Must call <computeroutput>MR_expected_void_std_string_Destroy()</computeroutput> to free it when you&apos;re done using it. </para>
